==English==
===Etymology===
{{webster}}

From [[w:Old English language|Old English]][[category:Old English derivations]] swepen; akin to [[w:Old English language|Anglo-Saxon]][[Category:Anglo-Saxon derivations]] swāpan. See [[swoop]]. 

===Pronunciation===
*swēp, /swiːp/, /<tt>swi:p</tt>/
*:[[Rhymes:English:-iːp|Rhymes: -iːp]]

=== Verb ===
{{irregverb|'''to sweep'''|'''[[sweeps]]'''|'''[[swept]]'''|'''[[swept]]'''|'''[[sweeping]]'''}}

# to [[clean]] using a [[broom]] or [[brush]]
# to move through an ([[horizontal]]) [[arc]] or similar long [[stroke]]
# to [[search]] [[methodically]]
# {{cricket}} to play a sweep shot
# {{curling}} To [[brush]] the [[ice]] in front of a moving [[stone]], which causes it to travel farther and [[curl]] less.

